bluefish-unstable (1.3.0-0dl1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release 1.3.0.
    - This release features a complete new highlighting engine.

  * debian/bluefish-unstable-data.install: Removed non-existent/used XML
    directory.
  * debian/bluefish-unstable-data.xmlcatalogs: Removed for the moment.
  * debian/control: Added Vcs-Svn after moving over to sf.net.
    (Vcs-Browser): Adjusted accordingly.
    (Build-Depends): Removed obsolete libgnomeui-dev, libgnomevfs2-dev,
    libxml2-utils and xml-core.
    (Description): Added note about development status.
  * debian/copyright: More complete copyright and license information.
  * debian/rules (binary-indep): Removed call to dh_installxmlcatalogs.
  * debian/README.Debian: Adjusted. Removed old comments for stable.

 -- Daniel Leidert (dale) <daniel.leidert@wgdd.de>  Sun, 14 Dec 2008 22:59:17 +0100

bluefish-unstable (1.1.6+cvs080509-0dl1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New test release from CVS 2008/05/09 (1.1.7 series).
    - Added option to select the match in the text search dialog.
    - Global session option to highlight a search result or select it.
    - Improvements to the drag and drop behaviour of the snippets plugin.
    - New "flat mode" for the filebrowser.
    - Improvements/fixes to the CSS highlighting pattern.
    - Several code fixes, cleanups and improvements.
    - Improvements of the highlighting engine (however, we will probably move
      to GtkSourceView and drop the self-written solution).

  * debian/control: Added Vcs-Browser field.
    (Build-Depends): Removed dpatch.
    (Depends): bluefish-unstable-dbg also contains the debugging symbols of
    bluefish-unstable-plugins.
    (Suggests): Added firefox for Ubuntu. 
  * debian/copyright: Small update.
  * debian/bluefish-unstable.install: Added stuff not in debian/tmp (removed
    it from debian/rules).
  * debian/bluefish-unstable-data.install: Ditto.
  * debian/bluefish-unstable-plugins.install: Ditto (further don't install .la
    files).
  * debian/bluefish-unstable-dbg.install: Ditto (initially added).
  * debian/rules: Removed dpatch related stuff.
    (config.status): Moved variables behind the configure call and added
    --disable-static to avoid building the statically linked plugins.
    (config.status, clean): Better copy config.* here instead in clean.
    (install): Removed stuff to install files from debian/ into the packaging
    directories (done by dh_install now).
    (binary-indep): List unconsidered files in debian/tmp.
    (binary-arch, binary-indep): Fix for older dh_desktop versions.

 -- Daniel Leidert (dale) <daniel.leidert@wgdd.de>  Fri, 09 May 2008 04:08:06 +0200

